('tt0011588','free','Pollyanna (1920)','1920','58min','The film opens in the Ozarks where a distraught Pollyanna (Mary Pickford) is comforting her father the Reverend John Whittier (Wharton James) as he dies.  After his death Pollyanna is sent to live on a New England plantation with her rich Aunt Polly (Katherine Griffith).
